Here's what you should include in pyproject.toml files:

- A script invocation:

```toml
[project.scripts]
# Maps the CLI command to your package's entrypoint
# If you use a src layout, your package module lives under src/your_package
pymc-llm-dev = "your_package.cli:main"
```

- A "src" layout for package discovery so you can do `uv pip install -e .`

```toml
[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=68.0.0"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"

[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
```

- A ruff section for configuring ruff

```toml
[tool.ruff]
target-version = "py313"
line-length = 100
src = ["src", "tests"]

[tool.ruff.lint]
select = ["E", "F", "I", "UP", "B"]
ignore = ["E203", "W503"]

[tool.ruff.format]
quote-style = "double"
indent-style = "space"
skip-magic-trailing-comma = false
```

- A pytest section for configuring pytest and automatic test discovery

```toml
[tool.pytest.ini_options]
python_files = ["test_*.py", "*_test.py", "*_tests.py"]
```
